Class SBSIHeaderDocument

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<SBSIHeaderDocument>
public class SBSIHeaderDocument
extends AbstractDocument
implements java.lang.Comparable<SBSIHeaderDocument>

This class encapsulates access to an SBSI Header file.
The method getSBSIHeader should only be called if hasErrors() is false.
In this manner, an ISBSIHeader object is always in a valid state.
To create a valid object, it is up to the client application to provide feedback to the user on how to update the document.
Typical usage would be : 

      if(!document.hasErrors) {
         ISBSIHeader header = document.getSBSIHeader();
         ....
       } else {
         //report errors
       }
This document represents an SBSI header file at the time it was first read; subsequent calls to getSBSIHeader() will return the same instance of the ISBSIHeader object each time, and will not reflect any editing of the file itself.

To get an up to date representation of a file, use :
SBSIResourceFactory.readHeaderFile(File headerFile); Equals() and hashcode() are not overriden, this means that identity is based on object identity. The reason that the file location is not used is that changes to the file content could result in multiple instances of an SBSIHeaderDocument that are considered equal (based on file location) but actually encapsulated different ISBSIHeader files.

Author:
Richard Adams /Neil Hanlon

makeListofHeaderDocumentsWithUniqueHeaderFiles

public static java.util.List<SBSIHeaderDocument> makeListofHeaderDocumentsWithUniqueHeaderFiles(java.util.List<SBSIHeaderDocument> headerDocuments)
Parameters:
headerDocuments -
Returns:
a list of header documents, each referring to unique header file SBSIHeaderDocuments refer to a 'snapshot' of a header file in time; therefore no two objects of this class are ever equals(). This method allows the construction of lists of SBSIHeaderDocuments where each document refers to a different header file, (ie, it has the same effect as if SBSIHeaderDocument DID implement equals based on name of the header file and the documents were stored in a set).

getSBSIHeader

public ISBSIHeader getSBSIHeader()
                          throws SBSIParseException
MEthod to retrieve an ISBSIHeader object. This object can only be created if the document is valid and has no errors. This method will return the same instance of the underlying ISBSIHeader object at each invocation.

Returns:
An ISBSIHeader object encapsulating the header file
Throws:
SBSIParseException - if document cannot be read properly
java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the document has errors (hasErrors()==true).
